}
```

4. Have the victim join a Teams live event/stream (which triggers HydraPlayer initialization).

5. Observe that:
   - The iframe created by `ee()` at line 25881 has NO `sandbox` attribute (verify in Electron DevTools)
   - The script from your attacker URL is fetched and loaded into the iframe
   - The `window.top` access succeeds (no sandbox restriction), giving full access to the parent Teams Electron calling context

